# An Introduction to Markdown 
Patrick Ruppert | Aptagen Webdaddy

---

## Markdown is a plain text markup syntax

* Can be written and viewed in any text editor
* Easy to read
* Easy to learn

---

## Why use Markdown?

* Future-proof
* Custom styling
* Export to multiple formats
* Content oriented

---

## How to Write Markdown

1. Open your preferred plain text editor
2. Save a new file with the `*.md` extension
3. Start writing!

---

## Basic Syntax

* Paragraphs
* Lists
* Inline formatting
* Block formatting

---

### Paragraphs

```
Lines written together are considered to be paragraphs.
You can start a new line and it will be attached to the previous paragraph.

Adding a blank line in between starts a new paragraph.
```

Lines written together are considered to be paragraphs.
You can start a new line and it will be attached to the previous paragraph.

Adding a blank line in between starts a new paragraph.

